Food and Beverage



Location

Baltimore, MD, US



Currency

USD



Founded

February 2014



Employees

5



Incorporation Type

LLC



Website

zesttea.com

















Company Summary





Winner of Best New Product at the World Tea Expo, Zest energy teas offer the energizing kick of coffee without the negative side effects. Despite our teas having comparable caffeine levels to coffee, the amino acids in Zest produce a steady and prolonged alertness, instead of the jitters and crash often associated with caffeinated products.
Zest has sold online since 2014 and launched into retail (Harris Teeter, Wegmans, Whole Foods) in 2016.










Team













James Fayal

Founder / CEO




James Fayal is a fellow with Venture for America and a 2012 graduate of the University of Maryland, where he graduated magna cum laude. His background is in venture capital (seed and series A) and entrepreneurial incubation. James started and ran a small manufacturing company in high school and returned to entrepreneurship to run Zest Tea in 2013. 












